text: Gros Morne National Park is a national park on the west coast of Newfoundland, Canada. It has been a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 1987. It has been a national park since 2005, and a national reserve since 1973. It has an area of , making it the second largest national park in Atlantic Canada. The park takes its name from a mountain in the area. Its name means "large mountain standing alone" in French. ==References== Category:World Heritage Sites in Canada Category:National parks in Canada Category:1973 establishments in Canada Category:Geography of Newfoundland and Labrador
